Smart Air Quality Sensor
This project is a Smart Air Quality Monitoring System that measures environmental parameters like CO₂, temperature, and humidity


Features
Monitors air quality using sensors like MQ135, PMS5003, or SDS011
Reads temperature & humidity with DHT22/BME280
Displays data on OLED/LCD screen
Sends data to the cloud via Wi-Fi (e.g., MQTT, HTTP)
Provides visual alerts for poor air quality

Hardware Requirements
Microcontroller (e.g., ESP32, ESP8266, Arduino Uno, or Raspberry Pi)
Air Quality Sensor (e.g., PMS5003, MQ135, SDS011)
Temperature & Humidity Sensor (e.g., DHT22, BME280)
Display (e.g., OLED SSD1306, LCD 16x2)
Power supply
Jumper wires and breadboard or PCB

Software Requirements
Arduino IDE / PlatformIO / Python (based on platform)
Required Libraries:
For Arduino: Adafruit_Sensor, DHT, MQUnifiedsensor, WiFi, PubSubClient, Adafruit_GFX, Adafruit_SSD1306
For Python: Adafruit_DHT, pms5003, RPi.GPIO, requests, etc.

Data Output
Real-time readings of:
PM2.5 / PM10 (µg/m³)
CO₂ (ppm)
Temperature (°C)
Humidity (%)
